FOR var FROM start TO (or DOWNTO) finish [STEP increment] DO command(s) END;\par
\par
Sets the variable var to start; then, while the value of this variable is less than or equal to (or greater than for DOWNTO) finish, it executes the commands and adds (or subtracts DOWNTO) 1 (or increments) to var.
